						"title": "Introducing the Cloudflare One Beta Program",
						"subtitle": null,
						"copy": "We are excited to announce the __Cloudflare One Beta Program__ – an opportunity for select customers to partner closely with our team in shaping Cloudflare's SASE roadmap and exploring new features and capabilities.\n\nExisting subscribers of any Zero Trust or Network services plan within __[Cloudflare One](https://www.cloudflare.com/cloudflare-one/)__ are eligible to participate.\n\nWhat customers can expect:\n- Early access to new features\n- An exclusive forum with direct access to Cloudflare Product and Engineering leaders\n- Roadmap previews and feedback sessions\n\nOur goal is to provide an open channel and direct feedback loops. To achieve that, we are deliberately starting with a limited number of participants. If you are interested, please let us know by completing the form to the right.\n\n---\n\n*Your use of any Beta Services made available through this program is governed by Cloudflare's Beta Services provision as defined in [Cloudflare's Enterprise Terms](https://www.cloudflare.com/enterpriseterms/) and [Self-Service Subscription Agreement](https://www.cloudflare.com/terms/), as applicable to your subscription.*\n\n*You agree not to post screenshots or otherwise publicly disclose information regarding new features or user interfaces that are made available to you through this program, and understand that such information is Cloudflare's confidential information.*",
